idt1CfgTable.name: idt1CfgTable
idt1CfgTable.description: This table contains an entry for each of the manageable T1-PRI ISDN Cards in the chassis. It contains objects that reflect the current configuration of parameters that affect the operation of all the entities that reside on the given card.

idt1CfgEntry.name: idt1CfgEntry
idt1CfgEntry.description: There is one Configuration table entry per T1-PRI ISDN Card in the chassis.

idt1CfgIndex.name: idt1CfgIndex
idt1CfgIndex.description: A unique value for each card in the chassis. The value of idt1CfgIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding card entity in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

idt1CfgAssgndISDNGateway.name: idt1CfgAssgndISDNGateway
idt1CfgAssgndISDNGateway.description: Identifies the NAS chassis slot of the Gateway Card assigned to this T1-PRI ISDN card. Range 0-16. Default=0(none).

idt1CfgMdmCallsAllowedEna.name: idt1CfgMdmCallsAllowedEna
idt1CfgMdmCallsAllowedEna.description: Indicates if modem calls are disabled/enabled for this T1-PRI ISDN Card. Default = enable(1).

idt1CfgMdmRoutingMethod.name: idt1CfgMdmRoutingMethod
idt1CfgMdmRoutingMethod.description: Defines the mechanism used for modem call routing for this T1-PRI ISDN Card. Default = roundRobin(2).

idt1CfgProjectSelectionR2.name: idt1CfgProjectSelectionR2
idt1CfgProjectSelectionR2.description: This object lets user select E1 CAS project options. Default = mfcBkR2(3).

idt1CfgInfoMsgTimeOut.name: idt1CfgInfoMsgTimeOut
idt1CfgInfoMsgTimeOut.description: This object sets the time out delay in seconds between INFO messages. This parameter is effective if overlap rx mode is enabled. Default = 12

idt1CfgInbDNISLength.name: idt1CfgInbDNISLength
idt1CfgInbDNISLength.description: This objects sets the total number of digits expected in the inbound phone number. In the E1-PRI this only is effective when overlap rx mode is enabled. Default = 15

idt1CfgSelectCompanding.name: idt1CfgSelectCompanding
idt1CfgSelectCompanding.description: Select companding (alaw or ulaw) for use with PCM encoded data. Default = alaw(1).

idt1CfgAniNumberEnable.name: idt1CfgAniNumberEnable
idt1CfgAniNumberEnable.description: Allow the collection of A calling party phone number. This takes additional time, and is not allowed for all switches. Default = disable(2).

idt1CfgNoBptyMethod.name: idt1CfgNoBptyMethod
idt1CfgNoBptyMethod.description: This object sets the method for handling an incoming call when the B-party (Called Number) is not found within the <inPhoneNum> table.

idt1CfgMaxISDNGwyCalls.name: idt1CfgMaxISDNGwyCalls
idt1CfgMaxISDNGwyCalls.description: This object sets the maximum number of ISDN calls that can be terminated by the Gateway card. Default = 0.

idt1CrTable.name: idt1CrTable
idt1CrTable.description: This table contains an entry for each of the manageable T1-PRI ISDN Cards in the chassis. It contains objects that reflect the current call routing configuration of the card.

idt1CrEntry.name: idt1CrEntry
idt1CrEntry.description: There is one Call Routing Table entry per T1-PRI ISDN Card in the chassis.

idt1CrIndex.name: idt1CrIndex
idt1CrIndex.description: A unique value for each card in the chassis. The value of idt1CrIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

idt1CrPhNumIndex.name: idt1CrPhNumIndex
idt1CrPhNumIndex.description: This object is the index for one of the 48 inbound call routing objects for this card.

idt1CrInboundPhNum.name: idt1CrInboundPhNum
idt1CrInboundPhNum.description: This is one of the 48 inbound call routing phone numbers.

idt1CrInboundCallType.name: idt1CrInboundCallType
idt1CrInboundCallType.description: This is one of the 48 inbound call routing call types. Default = analog(1).

idt1PlTable.name: idt1PlTable
idt1PlTable.description: This table contains an entry for each of the manageable T1-PRI ISDN Cards in the chassis. It contains objects that reflect the current reserved resource pool to DNIS mapping.

idt1PlEntry.name: idt1PlEntry
idt1PlEntry.description: There is one Reserved Resuorce Pool ID to DNIS Mapping Table entry per T1-PRI ISDN Card in the chassis.

idt1PlIndex.name: idt1PlIndex
idt1PlIndex.description: A unique value for each card in the chassis. The value of idt1PlIndex matches the value of the index for the corresponding card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

idt1PlIDIndex.name: idt1PlIDIndex
idt1PlIDIndex.description: This object is the index for one of the 12 pool IDs for this card.

idt1PlDNIS.name: idt1PlDNIS
idt1PlDNIS.description: This is the DNIS number associated with the POOL ID.

idt1PlType.name: idt1PlType
idt1PlType.description: This object is the pool type associated with the pool ID.

idt1MdmRPATable.name: idt1MdmRPATable
idt1MdmRPATable.description: This table contains an entry for each of the manageable T1-PRI ISDN Cards in the chassis. It contains objects that reflect the current Pool Assignment of the Pool Id to the modem device.

idt1MdmRPAEntry.name: idt1MdmRPAEntry
idt1MdmRPAEntry.description: There is one Reserved Pool Assignment to modem device Table entry per T1-PRI ISDN Card in the chassis.

idt1MdmRPAIndex.name: idt1MdmRPAIndex
idt1MdmRPAIndex.description: A unique value for each card in the chassis. The value of idt1MdmRPA Index matches the value of the index for the corresponding card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

idt1MdmRPAIDIndex.name: idt1MdmRPAIDIndex
idt1MdmRPAIDIndex.description: This object is the index for one of the 64 channel IDs for this card.

idt1MdmRPASlot.name: idt1MdmRPASlot
idt1MdmRPASlot.description: The channel associated with the Id of Modem device Reserved resource Pool Assignment table.

idt1MdmRPAChan.name: idt1MdmRPAChan
idt1MdmRPAChan.description: The slot associated with the Id of Modem device Reserved resource Pool Assignment table.

idt1MdmRPAPoolID.name: idt1MdmRPAPoolID
idt1MdmRPAPoolID.description: The Pool Id assigned in the Modem device Reserved resource Pool Assignment table (1/2/3/4 <-> none/A/B/C/D).

idt1GwyRPATable.name: idt1GwyRPATable
idt1GwyRPATable.description: This table contains an entry for each of the manageable T1-PRI ISDN Cards in the chassis. It contains objects that reflect the current Pool Assignment of the Pool Id to the ISDN-Gateway(s).

idt1GwyRPAEntry.name: idt1GwyRPAEntry
idt1GwyRPAEntry.description: There is one Reserved Pool Assignment to slot device Table entry per T1-PRI ISDN Card in the chassis.

idt1GwyRPAIndex.name: idt1GwyRPAIndex
idt1GwyRPAIndex.description: A unique value for each card in the chassis. The value of idt1GwyRPA Index matches the value of the index for the corresponding card's entry in the entity table of the chassis MIB.

idt1GwyRPASlotIndex.name: idt1GwyRPASlotIndex
idt1GwyRPASlotIndex.description: This object is the index for one of the 16 Slots in the chassis.

idt1GwyRPAPoolID.name: idt1GwyRPAPoolID
idt1GwyRPAPoolID.description: The Pool Id assigned in the ISDN-Gateway device Reserved resource Pool Assignment table (1/2/3/4 <-> none/A/B/C/D).
